## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
The existing spec files are scaffolded but empty. No existing tests cover auth. After implementation:

```bash
cd "c:\Users\amine\Desktop\Liadtech\personel project\Ai Car Rental\backend"
npm run test
```
This will run Jest on all `*.spec.ts` files to verify no compilation errors.

### Manual Verification (after configuring .env & running `prisma migrate dev`)
1. Start the server: `npm run start:dev`
2. Send a `POST` to `http://localhost:3000/auth/login` with body `{"email":"test@example.com","password":"password"}` using Postman or curl.
3. Expect a `401 Unauthorized` (user doesn't exist yet) or a `{ "access_token": "..." }` JWT on success.
4. Decode the JWT at [jwt.io](https://jwt.io) to verify it contains `userId`, `email`, and `role`.
